  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7035 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7015 and the massive +11.8B gamma wall at 7050, dealers are in a critical hedging zone where they'll aggressively sell any push toward 7050 while providing support above 7015. The PIN regime with 115B+ in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion setup, but the recent wall_break event and 3.5% 5-min move suggests we're testing the upper boundary of this gamma pocket. Watch 7050 as the key resistance where dealer selling pressure intensifies, and 7000 as the next major support level with 9B+ in positive gamma.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect strong resistance near 7050 with likely pullback toward 7000-7015 range.",
